<font color="#FF0000">AMNESTY FOR DRAFT EVADERS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 13 23:48:19 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
One protest issue that really burns in my mind was the amnesty given to Vietnam War draft evaders in 1975(I think I have the year right).<br><br>
I can think of no greater invalidation for what we experienced, did, obeyed, and served, than to have a President, a Commander in Chief, reward people who broke the law and ran away by letting them come back again to play.<br><br>
That really sends a message, doesn't it?<br><br>
Any comments? Any thoughts? I need to try to clear this one out of my mind. It *really* bugs me. Has anyone delt with this issue succesfully? 
